Blood bike app features and walkthrough: 

Cloud storage = aws 

Backend = golang + typescript 

Frontend = angular  

App is a pwa 

 

App begins at a login page  

From here the user is able to sign in 

Each user is assigned a role , this role is allocated by the admin . The admin has the power to change this roles along with account creation for new users . Users can have multiple roles , so when they log in theyll have a bar at the top of the screen to switch between there roles to display different pages. 

 

The role dictates what the user is able to see and access after they have logged in . 

 

Admin : can create accounts , assign roles , handle password recovery ,  

 

Rider: access to the maps page , jobs page and qr scanner to access the starting of a job/ride , access to see what vehicles are available at the depos as when a rider starts a job it places the vehicle into on a job mode meaning it doesnt appear available at depos to other riders . Rider are able to click active mode or unavailable so that dispatchers can see who is currently available to do jobs and who is unavailable(ie they are at work) 

 

Fleet Manager : See a active list of the vehicle fleets location , the amount of time they have been on the road since last service , who last had the bike , which depo it is stored at , if the bikes out on a job it will display who currently has ownership of it .Theyll also have a option when scanning a qr code to place the bike in service mode meaning it is taken away from being avaiable at depos so riders know what bikes are available and where , then he can scan it again to make it available again and can fill in a report on the service resetting the counters  

 

 

Dispatchers : access to creating a new job/run . They recieve contact from a hospital and then can create a listing for a run for riders to choose to accept . They can also view what riders are available , who are on call ,  who are not active . They have access to the map aswell and can see the depos and what vehicles are where so that they can inform the rider what would be fastest or easiest to access . Theyll also have access to the weather to inform the rider if a van would be more appropriate than a motorbike . 

 

 

Features available regardless of roles : settings page , community event tab(theyre role will display beside there name when a event is created . Only the user who created the event and the admin can delete a posted event .  

 

 

Features explained: 

 

QR codes will be created as stickers that are then placed on the bikes . The rider will have access to scan the bike qr code. They can then click start run which will then place the bike into busy mode to the other users . This then starts tracking live data , counting the hours spent on the road , km traveled since last service and if at the end of the ride the user scans the qr code again , can make the bike available , report a issue . They also state which depo the bike is being stored at . 